HEADWORD: Havildar
<hw>Hav`il*dar"</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧v`⟦icr⟧l*d⟦aum⟧r")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>In the British Indian armies, a noncommissioned
officer of native soldiers, corresponding to a sergeant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Havildar major</b></col>, <cd>a native sergeant major in
the East Indian army.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

